00:48:29.300 --> 00:48:31.459
Figuring out your boundaries, not saying yes to everything.

00:48:31.459 --> 00:48:33.060
I've learned that over the years.

00:48:33.060 --> 00:48:34.260
In the beginning, you're hungry, right?

00:48:34.260 --> 00:48:35.300
You're saying yes to everything.

00:48:35.300 --> 00:48:37.620
You're like, I need to pay the bills and eat.

00:48:37.620 --> 00:48:40.260
And eventually, you can pick and choose things.

00:48:40.260 --> 00:48:44.580
And I think we're really starting to hone in now on a lot of shiny work.

00:48:44.580 --> 00:48:46.179
We're really focusing there.

00:48:47.379 --> 00:48:55.139
Where we excel is helping the business answer questions with data and tying that gap.

00:48:56.820 --> 00:49:00.820
There's just such a skills gap between people that can live in Excel and do so much stuff

00:49:00.820 --> 00:49:01.139
there.

00:49:01.139 --> 00:49:07.699
But then that lift going to something like R or Python is just, you're like a superstar.

00:49:07.699 --> 00:49:09.699
And you can do so much so fast.

00:49:09.699 --> 00:49:11.459
And people have asked me at jobs.

00:49:11.459 --> 00:49:13.860
They come over to my desk and say, how did you generate that plot so fast?

00:49:13.860 --> 00:49:15.459
I'm like, R and ggplot.

00:49:15.459 --> 00:49:17.060
And then they become a believer too.

00:49:18.739 --> 00:49:24.179
So anyway, yeah, I think that we're starting to focus a lot more on what we're really good at.

00:49:24.179 --> 00:49:26.340
And it's been seven years.

00:49:26.340 --> 00:49:27.459
So it takes time.

00:49:31.459 --> 00:49:37.459
I love those examples of things being so much faster with R and showing how you can do it.

00:49:37.459 --> 00:49:45.379
But I'm curious if there's someone who's listening and who's the only R user at their company.

00:49:46.020 --> 00:49:48.899
And they're trying to get people on board.

00:49:48.899 --> 00:49:50.179
That's been me.

00:49:50.179 --> 00:49:51.300
That's been me a lot of times.

00:49:52.100 --> 00:49:53.620
Oh, I see Lisa's waving too.

00:49:55.540 --> 00:49:57.139
Yeah, so bless ggplot.

