00:52:23.540 --> 00:52:29.780
wide, but instead of having like a million row cap or 5 million row cap, they could do

00:52:29.780 --> 00:52:31.780
this with a billion rows.

00:52:33.459 --> 00:52:35.219
They're always super impressed.

00:52:35.219 --> 00:52:41.060
And then just like all the manual work that they have to do on a monthly basis for month

00:52:41.060 --> 00:52:48.739
end close or quarter end, seeing how you can automate a lot of that to just take out most

00:52:48.739 --> 00:52:54.260
of the manual work, I think impresses a lot.

00:52:54.260 --> 00:52:59.699
And then just like shiny apps, like everyone's saying, or R&D presentations that are just

00:52:59.699 --> 00:53:04.340
knitted to HTML or websites, like jarring on websites.

00:53:04.340 --> 00:53:11.780
These are things that if you're comfortable with R&D, like jumping to those websites is

00:53:12.419 --> 00:53:13.219
pretty easy.

00:53:13.219 --> 00:53:18.419
And then seeing how you can automate all the elements within those websites also impresses

00:53:18.419 --> 00:53:18.919
people.

00:53:19.459 --> 00:53:19.959
So.

00:53:21.139 --> 00:53:21.699
All right.

00:53:21.699 --> 00:53:22.340
Yeah.

